{
  "texts": [
    "The statistics of these datasets are summarized in Table 1.",
    "Open-Domain Dialogue (ODD) We select Dai-lyDialog (Li et al., 2017), a widely-used dataset of human-human dialogues crawled from various websites used by English learners to practice.",
    "The final dataset contains 13k written dialogues with an average of 8 turns per dialogue.",
    "Knowledge-Grounded Dialogue (KGD) We experiment on Wizard of Wikipedia (Dinan et al., 2019), a dataset of dialogues between two participants with the roles of apprentice and wizard.",
    "At each turn, the wizard can access a set of documents (passages from Wikipedia) and use it to incorporate factual knowledge in their reply."
  ]
}